In Potipharâ€™s house, Josephâ€™s faithfulness resulted in his being put in charge of everything. Later, in jail, he helped his fellow prisoners, earning a trust that ultimately led to his being put in charge of all of Egypt, second only to Pharaoh. 3. He was not wealthy, but theÂ apostle PaulÂ was perhaps the most famous Christian ever to live. How did his fame become worldwide and timeless? Paulâ€™s ambition was never to become famous or gather the accolades of men. His burning ambition was to do Godâ€™s work and glorify Christ. That was his higher calling.

InÂ Matthew 6:10â€“20, Jesus teaches us not store up treasures on earth, but in heaven. Then He says, â€œYou cannot serve both God and moneyâ€ (verse 24). And â€œSeek first his kingdom and his righteousness, and all these things [the basic necessities of life] will be given to you as wellâ€ (verse 33). That is, stop trying to be rich and famous, and instead simply seek after God, living out His purposes for your life. If God wants earthly riches to come your way, they will.

For those whose ambition is to be rich, the Bible has many cautions. Jesus said that it is difficult for the rich to enter the kingdom of heaven (Matthew 19:24).
